  "@context": "../../context.jsonld",
  "@type": "Process",
  "critical": false,
  "description": "Composting with Eisenia fetida (red wiggler) earthworms to produce vermicompost and worm castings. Worm castings contain 1.5-2.5% N, 1.0-1.5% P, and 1.0-1.5% K — significantly richer than thermophilic compost. Worm populations double every 2-3 months under ideal conditions, and worm tea serves as a potent liquid fertilizer.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Small-scale vermicomposting can be established in weeks with a bucket of worms and household food scraps, producing premium fertilizer continuously.",
